----

==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''got'', akin to Old Saxon ''god''
===Noun===
'''Gott''' ''m'' or ''n'' (''plural'' Götter)

# [[god]]

===Proper noun===
'''Gott'''

# [[God]]

===Usage notes===
The word was neuter in Old High German, but Christianity shifted the word to masculine, and necessitated the creation of a separate word ([[Göttin]]) for ''goddess''.  Thus in Christian contexts the word is usually masculine, while in Heathen ones it is usually neuter.

